  "text": "Apache Flink's windowing API provides extension points through abstract base classes and interfaces that developers must implement to create custom window assigners and triggers.\n\n## 1. WindowAssigner (Base Class)\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/WindowAssigner.java\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class WindowAssigner<T, W extends Window> implements Serializable`\n\n**Abstract Methods (Extension Points):**\n- `public abstract Collection<W> assignWindows(T element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context)` - Called to assign zero or more windows to an incoming element\n- `public abstract Trigger<T, W> getDefaultTrigger()` - Returns the default trigger for this window assigner\n- `public abstract TypeSerializer<W> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)` - Returns a serializer for windows produced by this assigner\n- `public abstract boolean isEventTime()` - Returns true if windows are based on event time, false for processing time\n\n## 2. MergingWindowAssigner (Subclass for Session Windows)\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/MergingWindowAssigner.java\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class MergingWindowAssigner<T, W extends Window> extends WindowAssigner<T, W>`\n\n**Additional Abstract Method:**\n- `public abstract void mergeWindows(Collection<W> windows, MergeCallback<W> callback)` - Determines which windows should be merged and invokes the callback to signal the merge operations\n\n**Supporting Interface:**\n- `MergeCallback<W>` with method `void merge(Collection<W> toBeMerged, W mergeResult)` - Called to merge windows\n\n## 3. Trigger (Lifecycle Callback Base Class)\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/triggers/Trigger.java\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class Trigger<T, W extends Window> implements Serializable`\n\n**Core Lifecycle Methods (Abstract):**\n- `public abstract TriggerResult onElement(T element, long timestamp, W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception` - Called when an element is added to a pane\n- `public abstract TriggerResult onProcessingTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception` - Called when a processing-time timer fires\n- `public abstract TriggerResult onEventTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception` - Called when an event-time timer fires\n- `public abstract void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception` - Called when a window is purged to clean up state\n\n**Merging-Related Methods (Optional):**\n- `public boolean canMerge()` - Returns false by default; override to return true if trigger supports merging\n- `public void onMerge(W window, OnMergeContext ctx) throws Exception` - Called when windows are merged; must be overridden if canMerge() returns true\n\n## 4. EventTimeSessionWindows (Reference Implementation)\n**Location:** flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/EventTimeSessionWindows.java\n\n**Class:** `public class EventTimeSessionWindows extends MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>`\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- **assignWindows()** - Creates a single TimeWindow for each element: `return Collections.singletonList(new TimeWindow(timestamp, timestamp + sessionTimeout));`\n- **mergeWindows()** - Delegates to TimeWindow utility: `TimeWindow.mergeWindows(windows, c);`\n- **getDefaultTrigger()** - Returns `EventTimeTrigger.create()`\n- **isEventTime()** - Returns `true`\n- Constructor accepts `long sessionTimeout` parameter defining the session gap\n\n## 5. TimeWindow (Window Representation)\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java\n\n**Class:** `public class TimeWindow extends Window`\n\n**Core Structure:**\n- Constructor: `public TimeWindow(long start, long end)` - Creates window with inclusive start and exclusive end\n- `public long getStart()` - Returns inclusive start timestamp\n- `public long getEnd()` - Returns exclusive end timestamp\n- `public long maxTimestamp()` - Returns `end - 1` (largest inclusive timestamp)\n- `public boolean intersects(TimeWindow other)` - Checks if windows overlap or touch\n- `public TimeWindow cover(TimeWindow other)` - Returns minimal window covering both windows\n\n**Utility Methods:**\n- `public static void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` - Merges overlapping windows by sorting and grouping\n- `public static long getWindowStartWithOffset(long timestamp, long offset, long windowSize)` - Calculates window start for tumbling/sliding windows\n\n## Extension Point Chain\nTo implement a custom window assigner, developers follow this pattern:\n1. Extend `WindowAssigner` (or `MergingWindowAssigner` for session-style windows)\n2. Implement `assignWindows()` to create TimeWindow instances\n3. For merging assigners, implement `mergeWindows()` to determine which windows should merge\n4. Optionally extend `Trigger` to implement custom trigger logic with lifecycle callbacks\n5. Specify the trigger via `getDefaultTrigger()` or override at usage time\n\nThe `EventTimeSessionWindows` class demonstrates this pattern: it extends `MergingWindowAssigner`, creates `TimeWindow` objects with gap-based logic, and reuses `TimeWindow.mergeWindows()` for window merging logic."
}

